Some rules and approximations need to be followed when designing an LCL filter. One of which is that the inductor voltage drop should not exceed 5–10% of the network root-mean-square of the rated voltage [14], whereas the current ripples should not be more than 25% of the rated current. In most cases, it lies within the range of 15–25% [1, 4]. Lastly, the reactive power absorbed by the capacitor (Qc) should be less than the generated active power (Pg). With the help of the above assumptions, the below expressions are derived.15ILmax∗XL=ILmax∗2πLf<0.05∗Vin\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
